Ona—This genus consists of between twenty and thirty species of strong-growing Ferns, generally with mem- braneous flaccid fronds. They are widely distributed throughout the West Indies, Tropical America, West Africa, Mauritius, Ceylon, India, Malayan, Philippine, and Polynesian Islands.
